Philosophical chemistry is a science of
late origin and that part of it which
relates to Agriculture is still in an
infant state but it has nevertheless already
afforded many interesting facts and it
is connected with investigation of very
great importance.
In attempting to give an account
of the connection of Chemistry with
agriculture - I shall endeavour to follow
that order of arrangement which begins
with the least obscure part of the [deletion]sup[/deletion]
