The great object of the chemistry
of agriculture is the discovery of the best
possible manner of cultivating different
lands so as to produce upon them the
greatest quantity of useful plants -
This object which at first view
might appear simple is in fact very
complicated and is connected with a
great variety of scientific generalizations

